cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use NemulAI in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "NemulAI: Per-Job GPU Cost Attribution and Waste Detection"
abstract: >
  NemulAI is an open-source Python agent for real-time GPU cost attribution,
  per-job and per-team energy accounting, and idle/underutilization waste
  detection in AI/ML infrastructure. It samples power draw via NVML
  (nvidia-ml-py) and vendor SDKs for AMD, Intel, and Apple Silicon, attributes
  energy cost to individual training and inference jobs, and prices it at the
  operator's GPU rate. Read-only by default.
authors:
  - name: "NemulAI"
    website: "https://nemulai.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/AgentMulder404/NemulAI"
url: "https://nemulai.com"
license: Apache-2.0
version: "0.4.0"
date-released: "2026-06-18"
keywords:
  - GPU cost attribution
  - waste detection
  - energy monitoring
  - chargeback
  - MLOps
  - NVML
  - nvidia-ml-py
  - AI infrastructure
